stem:
What is printed by the following code?

```java
int x = -9;
System.out.println(Math.abs(x) - 3);
```

What is printed by the following code?

```java
double r = Math.sqrt(25);
System.out.println(r);
```

What is printed by the following code?

```java
double a = Math.abs(-4.0);
double b = Math.pow(a, 2);
double c = Math.sqrt(b);
System.out.println(c);
```

What is printed by the following code?

```java
int x = (int) Math.sqrt(100);
int y = (int) Math.pow(2, 3);
System.out.println(x / y + x % y);
```

What are the values of `x` and `y` after the following code executes?

```java
double x = Math.pow(3, 2) - Math.abs(-5);
int y = (int)(x / 2);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = Math.abs(-8);
int y = Math.abs(5);
System.out.println(x + y);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
double result = Math.pow(2, 4);
System.out.println((int) Math.sqrt(result));
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = -7;
double y = 2.0;
System.out.println(Math.abs(x) + Math.pow(y, 3));
```

Determine the output of the following code segment:

```java
int x = -3;
double y = Math.pow(x, 2);
double z = Math.sqrt(49);
int result = (int)(Math.abs(-4.8) + z);
System.out.print((int)y + " " + result);
```
